Class Summary
AttributeTable A simple java bean that encapsulates data from actual attribute table from KML file that contains only the name value pairs that correspond to allowable items specified in the config.

BaseApp To be subclassed by a commandline app and possibly a gui app
CommandLineApp Commandline application to conversion of geographic datafiles to KML using ogr2ogr write timespan or timestamp values to the new KML time fields The Configuration of application runs is based on a configuration file
FixedKmlTimeSource Implementation to provide way of using a fixed date values for a KmlRewriter Calls default base class constructor because parsers aren't needed
KmlRewriter  
KmlTimeData A simple data transport object containing KML time data The data elements are Strings expected to conform to ISO8601 Both timespan (a pair of values) and timestamp (a single value) are supported by the same class.
KmlTimeSource Implementations will, as delegates of a KmlRewriter, provide the time/date data object to the rewriter.
LabelList Lists for begin and end labels, to match against in rewriting KML treats list items as regex
